description:
View the original video with the original AGNES OBEL music here:
https://old.bitchute.com/video/gh7bnm5jWzKT/
OR on my blog:
https://koudekaas.blogspot.com/
Then go to my blog post named "Part 3 with all the PHOTOS [..]'  or to the post (just copy paste this after my blog address) 2019/11/all-photos-in-video-format-with.html
All the publicly known photos are here, in the correct order (verified with ImperfectPlan - this happened after I uploaded the above video, sigh..): https://koudekaas.blogspot.com/2019/12/the-disappearance-of-kris-kremers-and_11.html There are more photos, but they are being held back by the families, authorities and by the people (authors/sleuths) who also have copies of them through the case files; they do not want to publish them. My blog about this disappearance case: https://koudekaas.blogspot.com/

Recently my original version of this video was blocked by Youtube. It had been up for over three years without issue, using two songs: 'Wonderful Life' from Black and 'The Curse' from Agnes Obel. It is that 2nd song which has been flagged by PIAS music. A real shame, as it is a very fitting song many believe. I reuploaded the video with a different song here, something rather obscure. The two blocked videos had hundreds of comments and discussions below it. I have screen saved many of them and uploaded them on my blog. I know that people are invested in this case and often made an effort and used their time to comment, so it feels a shame to just see all those comments gone now. You can find them here: https://koudekaas.blogspot.com/2017/03/rest.html
See my comprehensive blog about this case: https://koudekaas.blogspot.com/  

MORE INFO: 
-These photos were partly published by the families, by the authorities and in the media over time. There are still some photos left which have not been made public. They include some photos on the Pianista (a few selfies and landscapes, similar to the photos we do have) and a couple of night photos that are almost entirely black. People who have seen them all, including the families, Imperfect Plan & Jeremy Kryt, have verified that there is nothing of interest to be seen on those photos other than blackness and some droplets. 

-The night photos were leaked to Juan and then to me. Versions with a date and time stamps on them, and identical versions without the time stamps. The daytime photos that were leaked do not have this info stamped on them.  

-Many of the night photos were brightened and/or rotated with a Photoshop type of program. This is a verified fact, first discovered by Juan and later confirmed by even Pitti and her team. This was done in Panama on June 17th, a few days before the camera and SD card were sent to the Dutch NFI, to do the first forensic investigation, which Pitti had delegated to them. We therefore know that the photo originals were manipulated to some extent by the case authorities in Panama, if only out of curiosity. We do not know to which extent they photoshopped them, or if they are perhaps responsible for the thoroughly deleted file 509. 

-The Canon camera was still set to 2013 instead of 2014, and was also 6 hours off. This was confirmed by police, who had to recalculate the time and who did so based on coordinating the photo times of the mobile phone photos and based on the time seen on a wristwatch pictured on one of the photos, reportedly. The camera was set to London time (GMT), which was six hours ahead of Panama on April 1st of 2014. Kris and Lisanne seem to have never adjusted the time when arriving in Panama and neither did they change its 2013 setting to 2014. 

-Please keep this in mind however: We don't have the evidence that police recalculated these times correctly. Even the times police came up with do not match with the many witness testimonies. Read my blog or check Juan's channels for more info about all this. 

-Kris and Lisanne seem to have simply only pressed the photo taking button on their digital Canon Powershot SX270HS camera with battery and without a lens cap  They did not reset the correct time or date and they also did not change photo taking settings. 

#KrisandLisanne #KrisKremers #LisanneFroon

comments.text: I have an honest question for other folks online; is there anyone else who is deeply, heavily, hopelessly attached to this case on an emotional and almost spiritual level? I know there are a lot of conspiracy-minded individuals that want to prove their new and unique theory about fowl-play is the correct one; I feel anyone that is reasonable and knows all the facts of the case knows this was a tragic accident. That being said, every few years I am drawn back to Lisanne and Kris and that nightmare in the jungle. At first it feels like it's just a morbid curiosity that will pass after watching the new video that just popped up in my feed but in reality I just feel so deeply connected to both of them and I end up crying in private for days. At this point, I feel like 'how could you not?' This is by far one of the saddest stories I've ever come across. They were both such kind hearted, exceptional human beings... and I resent the cruel nature of this world that lured them in with it's beauty only to reduce them to... well, a foot in a shoe and half a pelvic bone.

comments.text:
The village woman who claimed to have found Kris and Lisanne's backpack on a riverbank when she went there to wash her clothes. She also said the backpack was definitely not there a day before. 

What does that mean ?

As far as I know, the walking time on foot from her house to the river is two hours. That means she will require at least four hours (round trip) plus time required for washing. I believe she required a total of at least six hours to do the job and she was allegedly alone in the wilderness .  6 hours or more .

My question is :  How likely was it that she herself being alone as a female went to a far away place to wash her clothes on two CONSECUTIVE days ? 

Why didn't she do the work in one day with a partner ?  

I cannot understand her mindset and I do not believe she is telling the truth. 
It is just unusual . There was no eye witness and she could say anything she wants. How can she say the backpack was "definitely" not there yesterday. 

 Don't forget she was actually Feliciano's employee working at his coffee farm .

She lied.
comments.author: @Sandoz-tq7qj

comments.text:
I know this case for a few years now but never dug deeper into it. First of all, it's, like all of them, a sad case. Especially if you see the pictures. While digging deeper into the case I'm currently hearing the "Lost in Panama" Podcast and these pictures here are a huge help when it comes to visual understanding. The next thing I will read is the still fresh book by the two german Authors and what could be seen as a follow-up to the Podcast and is called "Still Lost in Panama" (I know they released also an english edition of this).

I'm really no True Crome Detective sleuth so what comes now is just my own interpretation of what I gained from reading and listening about the case of Kris and Lisanne. In my own opinion, I really think people want to see something very sinister here. People want a candyman like this tour guide who plotted all of this and they want a conspiracy that a whole village was involved with this. While this keeps the mystery going I'm honest, I really think this was an accident, a very horrible tour of both women that had hone very wrong. If you are in search of a culprit, name the Jungle. Both women strolled way too far away from the path. That's a fact and everybody knows this. I've took a walk while I was on vacation at the german Nordsee and just strolled, maybe 200 meters, a little too far from the visitors path and landed literally in the Wadden Sea which can be as merciless like the Jungle if you are on your own without a guide. I paniced, got lost but gladly was able to find the way again. If I had gone even further I've might not found a way back.

From my current standpoint of knowledge (and I'm still listening to the Podcast and must read the book), there is not much that tells me that foul play is a valid option. Indeed, a lot of things in this case are very strange especially that the whole village acts like that this is Twin Peaks. But on the other hand, why act people so weird in Boquete? Criminal rate and corruption is, of course, high in Latin America. But Boquete was even 2014 a tourist hot spot. It's way bigger nowadays. People act like this, and maybe this sounds disappointing now, because, talking about this well known case might simply be bad for business. Bad for the trail, the tour guides making a living there and of course hotels and other local attractions like restraurants and so on.

Anyway, just wanted to leave my 2 Cents here. Maybe I will change my mind aftter knowing the whole story. But I already reached the point in the Podcast where they are going in circles and running into dead ends. I would love to see a real closure for the families of Kirs and Lisanne. But maybe we have the answer for years now. Of course there are still so many unanswered questions left. Just because my theory is that this really was an accident, we still don't know what happened to them and how they end up deep in the jungle for so many days.

Cheers and best wishes from Germany, neighbour of the Netherlands.
comments.author: @TheAufziehvogel

comments.text:
No fool play.
In the end, I think they let themselves be trapped by the arrival of night.
After photo 508, I think Lisanne dropped her camera on the ground or in the water. Making it unusable. Despite everything, they continued a little on the trail and at one point they decided to go back but they saw that the light was dropping very quickly in certain portions since we are in the tropics and the sun rises at 6:00 in the morning and goes to bed at 6:00 p.m. all year round.
They are therefore on their way back but they realize that they need at least two or three hours of walking and a large part of this walk will have to take place at night. They worry because they know the places they have already passed and know that without a flashlight, in the dark of night, it is very difficult and distressing.
Thats when they try to call for help, if only to say where they are because they didnt tell anyone in the end. They just said they were going for a walk.
But impossible to contact anyone: no network.
At that moment, they were not injured, nor pursued by anyone, just anxious at the idea of returning at night. The wisest thing would have been to land somewhere in open ground and resolve to spend the night there and leave the next morning at first light. In a video, the mother of Kriss who came on the trail explains that she is absolutely sure that if one of the girls had been injured, they would have stayed on the trail and waited. The problem actually is that he There was no injury or other, only from being trapped by the time and the arrival of night, and also from not having warned anyone.

I think that by trying to retrace the path at night, she had a high chance of getting lost, falling, slipping, etc. Which at night reinforces the seriousness of the situation.
So they get lost. And the second catastrophe arrives, no one knows where they went or more precisely, no one knows that they continued beyond the Mirador, towards the North on the path. So by the time we organize the research, a lot of time will pass. And we will have to wait until April 6 for research to be done on the other side of the Mirador. That is to say that the girls got lost, that they continued to move during these 6 days, if only to try to find a place with a little network. And obviously in 6 days, without food or very little (?), without water except that of the river (risk of diarrhea that one of the girls already had not long before during the stay), without being able to make a fire. Fear, anxiety, stress, exhaustion...etc. When the search begins beyond the Mirador, the girls are already in a bad state in my opinion.

On April 8, they have been in the jungle for 7 days! It is said that you can survive 3 minutes without breathing, 3 days without drinking and 3 weeks without eating. I think they were in the state of people who go on hunger strike. They must have remained in bed, half lucid. One may be more affected than the other.
On the night of April 8, they heard noise, perhaps light signals in the sky or something else coming from the search teams. I think Lisanne understands that you have to try something to stand out. They are obviously in no condition to scream or anything. So she takes out the camera which she had put to dry and which she had not tried to get it working again since. And it works again. This is possible if the device fell into water and was quickly removed from the water. In time he can works again. So she decides to use it to make flash shots towards the sky. Obviously it takes photos at the same time but the goal is the flash.
She is exhausted and at the same time held by the hope of being seen. She awkwardly directs the flash towards the ground a few times which causes her to accidentally take a photo of Kriss' hair who is probably lying sleepy next to her or her head on Lisanne's legs.
But it doesn't work, the noises and signals go away. The only hope for days has vanished. We didn't see them.

I think they end up dying of exhaustion and hunger. Not necessarily at the same time.

Subsequently, the rainy season set in, causing rivers to swell and causing flooding. Their bodies were carried away by the waves, disintegrating as they decomposed....

RQ / *Contrary to what has often been said, the bag was dirty and damp when they found it. The items they contained were also damp and the devices were unusable. The Dutch experts had difficulty using them; it was easier with SD cards.
*The fact that the young women took off their bras appears normal  considering the conditions in which they were (heat, humidity, etc.).
*The shorts again were not found dry and folded neatly on a stone. It was dirty, wet and with holes.
*There have never been 70 pin code attempts in 1 day as has been said. In fact it was the Dutch experts who determined that since the phone was put into service, there had been 70 unsuccessful pin code attempts. That is to say that since the girl had been using her cell phone, it had happened to her 70 times of making a mistake when typing your code.
*There has never been a scrap of human flesh found with bones, which seemed impossible as decomposition would have made it disappear very quickly. In fact this scrap of flesh was analyzed and it was beef.
